                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d681">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13115: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-09T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 9, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received, June 9—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>254. Legation’s 245, June 6, 5 p.m. Following telegram has been received from
                    Vice Consul Yunnanfu: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“June 8, 10 a.m. Referring to my telegram of June 5, 3 p.m., American
                            citizens residing Tatsienlu are safe at Chungking.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
